<br>
'Here be Mammoths'<br>
<br>
Jeldar and I are akin, him an embodied spirit of the power of nature, earth magic and animal instincts. Me the physical representation.<br>
<br>
The hunt is wild, it cannot be tamed, it must evolve naturally to be one with Tunare's children. Tassius, proud and from the land of men understands this well, but never so well as I or Jeldar.<br>
<br>
We must seek the prey, hurd it to us, deliver it to a stand point to our advantage. We fight on their home land, in their environment, we must force them to adapt to us, not the other way around.<br>
<br>
We must bring the fight to them, and so it is with The Tainted ones. They more so are Wild, truly a child of Tunare. Beauty and the beast encampassed in one, Tassius' shout tinged with excitement is my call. Excitement at striving with Nature, the thrill of the Hunt, masters of our destiny we pit our arms and skills against the raw force of nature, to succeed or die is of no consequence.<br>
<br>
Jeldar has made his peace, his totem animal guiding his steps, fleet of foot and strong of shoulder. I ranging far into the icy wastes to track our prey and Tassius, dear Tassius, passion and strength incarnate more like nature than he would care to admit, more like the animal of his hunt. Wild and proud, Chaos constricted by Order. What else can Paladin be, Warrior Priest, Death with a Shroud, Divine Retribution.<br>
<br>
Strangely the Heart calms as The tainted one is drawn to us, Tassius linked with us, calmed by Jeldar. Mammalian reflexes kick in as I ease my self into a fast pace lope akin to my Wolf brothers to join with my Hunt brethren.<br>
<br>
The stench is foul, I can barely make out the spore of Tassius as I crest a glacier ridge and look upon the site below. Jeldar chanting in cross legged position, Tassius feet set wide apart, long two Handed blade now replaced his customeray single handed Ghoulbane. The tip of the sword placed into the snow at his feet, A Steel cross of Blade, guard and Hilt. Face set and shoulders back. The picture of Faith.<br>
<br>
Charging and snorting the beast came on, dank sweat marring it's russet coloured flanks, froth spraying into the air as it lifted its long muscular trunk and declared its own battle cry.<br>
<br>
Tass and I shared a mind touch he senced my Calm, my almost non-existant pulse beat. I shared with him again my joy and pride at our awareness of each other. He shared with me his passion and courage. We cast this into the teeth of Nature, at the feet of Tunare, onto the tusks of the Tainted one.<br>
<br>
Instinct is my guide in all things, and even as the tainted one screamed as my claws dug into it's side, and the warmth of its entrails made a mist of the snow, I could sence a danger here, a presence more vile than this tainted beast. Even as Tassius grinned up at me as he lopped of one tusk then another as our trophies, Jeldar and I both came on guard, the first time Jeldar had moved and quietly he whispered.<br>
'The Corrupted one comes, stand ready. I shall be your protector in this'<br>
<br>
The Hunt is wild, we who hunt must be wild too - it is our nature.<br>
<br>
 <p>Semdayen Maa'Sankari<Br>Ranger of the 29th Season<Br>In the Service of Tunare<Br><Br>'I am not lost - this is the scenic route'
